(42, 8, 9, 28, 6, 3, 3, 'What might this parable be?', 'Seeking Knowledge of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the disciples'' desire to understand Jesus'' teachings, paralleling the call in Hosea to pursue knowledge of the Lord. Both passages emphasize the importance of actively seeking understanding and following God''s ways.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 9, 41, 4, 34, 34, 'What might this parable be?', 'Disciples'' Inquiry and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' desire for understanding. In Luke, they ask about the parable, while in Mark, Jesus explains things to them when alone.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 9, 43, 15, 15, 15, 'What might this parable be?', 'Understanding Through Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowledge and understanding between Jesus and his followers. In both passages, the disciples seek understanding, and Jesus emphasizes that he shares knowledge with them, elevating their relationship from servants to friends.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 23, 6, 9, 9, 'seeing they might not see, and hearing', 'Understanding and Perception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hearing and seeing without understanding. They highlight the idea that some are given insight into divine mysteries while others remain blind and deaf to the truth.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 41, 4, 11, 11, NULL, 'Mysteries of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that understanding the mysteries of the kingdom of God is granted to some, while others receive teachings in parables. This connection highlights the distinction between those who are given insight and those who are not.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 40, 11, 25, 25, 'mysteries of the kingdom of God', 'Mysteries of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that understanding the mysteries of God is reserved for the humble rather than the wise. Luke highlights that knowledge is given to some while Matthew notes that these truths are hidden from the wise and revealed to ''babes.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 24, 5, 21, 21, NULL, 'Understanding and Perception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of people having eyes and ears yet failing to see and hear. This connection highlights the contrast between those who understand the mysteries of God and those who do not. The use of similar phrases underscores the lack of spiritual insight.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 23, 44, 18, 18, 'that seeing they might not see', 'Understanding and Perception in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of understanding and perception. Luke 8:10 speaks of the mysteries of the kingdom being revealed to some, while Isaiah 44:18 describes a lack of understanding due to God shutting their eyes.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 40, 13, 11, 17, 'mysteries of the kingdom of God', 'Mysteries of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''mysteries of the kingdom,'' highlighting the distinction between those who understand and those who do not. They also share similar phrases about seeing and hearing without understanding, reinforcing the theme of spiritual insight.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 10, 51, 2, 2, 2, 'mysteries of the kingdom of God', 'Mysteries of the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''mystery'' in both passages. Luke emphasizes the mysteries of the kingdom of God, while Colossians speaks of the mystery of God and Christ, suggesting a shared understanding of divine truths.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 40, 13, 19, 19, 'the seed is the word of God', 'Connection of Seed and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''seed'' representing the ''word'' of God. Luke 8:11 identifies the seed as the word of God, while Matthew 13:19 discusses the reception of this word in the heart.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 41, 4, 14, 20, NULL, 'Connection of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''the word'' being sown and its varying reception. Luke 8:11 states that ''the seed is the word of God,'' while Mark 4:14 refers to ''the sower soweth the word,'' illustrating the same theme of the word''s impact on different types of soil.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 59, 1, 21, 21, 'the word of God', 'Connection of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the word of God in spiritual growth and salvation. Luke describes the word as a seed, while James encourages the reception of the engrafted word, indicating its transformative power.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 60, 1, 23, 25, 'the word of God', 'Connection of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the enduring nature of the ''word of God.'' Luke 8:11 identifies the seed as the ''word of God,'' while 1 Peter 1:23-25 speaks of being born again by the ''word of God'' that ''liveth and abideth for ever.'' This connection highlights the transformative power and permanence of God''s message.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 23, 8, 20, 20, 'the word of God', 'Connection of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the word of God. Luke 8:11 identifies the seed as the word of God, while Isaiah 8:20 stresses adherence to this word as a source of light.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 11, 46, 3, 6, 7, 'the seed is the word of God', 'Connection of Growth and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the word of God in spiritual growth. Luke 8:11 identifies the seed as the word of God, while 1 Corinthians 3:6-7 illustrates how planting and watering relate to the growth that God provides.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 53, 2, 9, 14, 'lest they should believe and be saved', 'Connection of Deception and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of deception in preventing belief and salvation. In Luke, the devil takes away the word, while in 2 Thessalonians, strong delusion leads to believing a lie, hindering salvation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 40, 13, 19, 19, 'then cometh the devil, and taketh away', 'Connection of the Sower''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the devil in taking away the word from those who do not understand it. They describe the same scenario of the seed sown by the way side and the subsequent action of the wicked one.', 'parallel', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 59, 1, 23, 24, 'hear; then cometh the devil', 'Connection of Hearing and Action', 'This connection highlights the importance of not just hearing the word but also acting upon it. Both passages emphasize the consequences of failing to retain or apply the word, leading to a lack of belief and forgetfulness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 66, 12, 9, 9, 'the devil', 'Connection Between Devil and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the devil in deceiving and taking away belief. In Luke, the devil prevents belief and salvation, while in Revelation, he deceives the whole world.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 20, 1, 24, 26, 'lest they should believe and be saved', 'Rejection of God''s Word', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejecting God''s message. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the consequences of not heeding God''s call and the subsequent loss of salvation or protection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 41, 4, 15, 15, 'taketh away the word out of their hearts', 'Connection of Spiritual Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the immediate action of Satan in taking away the word from those who hear it. This highlights a common theme of spiritual opposition to belief and salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 12, 20, 4, 5, 5, 'the word out of their hearts', 'Wisdom and the Word', 'This connection highlights the importance of retaining the word in one''s heart, as seen in both passages. Luke 8:12 warns against losing the word, while Proverbs 4:5 encourages the pursuit of wisdom and understanding.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 13, 28, 6, 4, 4, NULL, 'Fleeting Faith and Commitment', 'Both passages emphasize the transient nature of faith and commitment. In Luke, believers receive the word with joy but lack depth, while in Hosea, the goodness of Ephraim and Judah is compared to a morning cloud that quickly vanishes.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 13, 43, 5, 35, 35, 'receive the word with joy', 'Joy and Temporary Faith', 'Both passages emphasize a temporary response to light and truth. In Luke, those who receive the word with joy lack depth and fall away, while in John, the people rejoice in the light for a season, suggesting a similar fleeting enthusiasm.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 8, 13, 20, 12, 12, 12, 'root', 'Roots and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''root'' in both passages. Luke discusses the lack of root leading to falling away, while Proverbs emphasizes that the root of the righteous yields fruit.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
